title: For Sale:  STAR 30MI STARFIRE SUPER RARE 1911 FULL SIZE 30
postcontent:
Hello, if your looking at this listing chances are you know what your looking at, but for the people not familiar with this, 1911 full frame/Spain made/military issue firearm,  it was the crown jewel of STAR industry.  The 30MI or 30m is a true tried and proven workhorse, one of those "I will never sell because it has a special place in my collection". I had it for years and it has never ever jammed/misfired/not gone boom!  Regardless of what ammo you put on it, 100% shot every time. Full metal body (run out of ammo hit them in the head) it has always been cleaned/lubed after use. If you dont know the history of Star, do yourself a favor and Google it ! Very rare to have one of these in the market, specialy in this shape and with 2 (original)  mags and grip. 

Here are some specs and features:
The Mod30-M is a SA/DA pistol. Length of pull in single action is .098 inches; that’s right folks, under one-tenth of an inch. It’s a smooth pull, breaking at 4.41 lbs. Emptying the 15 round magazine is simpler than snapping your fingers. Keep the hammer down, and double acti.  pull length is .472 inches and breaks at 7.94 lbs. Overall length is 8.07 inches, with a 4.33 inch barrel and a sighting line length of 6.3 inches. Using standard 115 grain FMJ loads, and stretching the pistol to it’s “effective rage” of 164 feet (50 meters), penetration depth of 3.94 inches was recorded in pine boards. In the interest of safety, the pistol incorporates an ambidextrous thumb safety which requires the shooter to move their hand from a firing position to physically work the safety. Additionally, the Mod30-M has a magazine safety which prevents the pistol from being fired with the magazine removed.

The sale is for the Firearm, 2 original 15 rds magazines, soft molded grip and carry case.. Buyer must have drivers license and be willing to sign bill of sale. CASH ONLY. Or trade for a CC 9mm. Not in a hurry to sell.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Pre-ban Ruger Mini 14 with bayonet, ammo, extras
postcontent:
This Series 182 Mini-14 is made to look as much like the M14 rifle as possible that Ruger modeled their famous rifle on.  The highlight is an M4-style bayonet (if you are aware of Mini 14's at all, you know what a big deal having a bayonet is) mounted on a BRAND NEW M4-style muzzle brake with winged front sight.  Other modifications on the rifle include a rear tech peep sight and a leather/web green sling.  Extras include:  original front blade sight (beat up a fair bit before I got it), Choate birdcage flash hider which slides over original front sight, five magazines (two metal 40 round, one OEM steel Ruger 20 round, one original Ruger 5 round, one BRAND NEW polymer ProMag 20 round), two BRAND NEW magazine couplers to connect magazines together for quicker mag changes, an extra magazine reinforcement bracket (if you want to be able to swap between two different stocks quickly), 100 rounds of loose .223 ammunition, and a soft rifle sleeve to protect the gun.  I have a handful more NIP Promag 20 round magazines I would sell, or throw in for the right trade.

I haven't fired it since installing the new sights/muzzle break so it will need to be sighted in on the range, but I did bore-sight it as well as possible using a laser so it shouldn't need too much adjustment.  This is an older, used rifle so there's some wear to it.  A few dings in the stock and butt, some wear on the bluing, etc.  There's also some deep scratches on the mounting handle on the bayonet where the hole had to be enlarged to fit over the muzzle brake.  But everything is in great working order, and this is a unique Mini-14 for your collection or use.

If you have any questions after reading this ad, feel free to drop me an e-mail.  I can send more pictures on request, or set up a time to meet.  I'm willing to do a little driving if you're coming from far away.  You must have a photo ID, and I prefer to deal with a CCW permit holder.  If you don't have a CCW permit, you must sign a bill of sale that I will provide and I reserve the right to do a background check before signing the bill of sale if I feel it's necessary.  

I would like cash, but am willing to entertain the idea of trades with cash up or down. title: For Sale:  ROGERS & SPENCER BLACK POWDER REVOLVER, VERY RARE!
postcontent:
This is a Very rare Revolver with only 5,000 ever made.  A number in existence to this day is still undetermined. The Rogers & Spencer Black Powder revolver was manufactured in the early 1860's and 5,000 were ordered by the U.S. Military. In 1865 by the time the order could be filled, the Civil War was coming to an end and the contract was canceled. The guns were sold off to an arms dealer by the name of Francis Bannerman as scrap after the government contract was canceled and Bannerman sold the gun to consumers throughout the first quarter of the 20th century. Its still argued that around 800 of the revolvers did see combat in the Civil War. This particular Rogers & Spencer Revolver bares the serial number of 3060 (which appears matching on all parts) and all government inspection stamps (RPB on the grip and the letter "B" stamped on metal parts). The Gun also bares the Rogers & spencer name stamped on the frame above the cylinder, along with Utica NY stamped underneath for where the gun was manufactured. The revolver is .44 cal with a 7 1/2" octagon barrel and is a single action. It has a smooth functioning action and minimal corrosion. The bluing has dissipated a fair amount from what looks to be everyday holster carry, which to a true collector definitely increases the cool factor!
